You are invited to participate in a research study being conducted by Kassandra Doran, B.S., a Master of Arts student at Brandeis University. The study is being supervised by Dr. Raymond Knight, PhD., Professor of Psychology. 

Please read this form carefully as it tells you about your rights. Please ask if you have any questions. If you decide to participate in this study you will be asked to indicate your consent at the bottom of the page.

What is this study about?
This study is looking at both impulsive and sexual behaviors. 

Why have we asked you to participate? 
We are asking you to take part in this study because you are over the age of 18.

What will you be asked to do if you participate?
This study will include answering a questionnaire on a computer. These questions will ask about yourself and your behaviors. 
The study will take you about 30 minutes to complete.

Are there any possible risks to you?
There is a low risk that your information could be accidentally shared with people not connected with this study, but your name will not be attached to your responses. 
If any questions make you feel uncomfortable, you can simply skip them and move to the next question.


Will you benefit from participating in the study?
You will not benefit directly by participating in this study. We hope that the research will result in a better understanding of impulsive and sexual behavior.

Will it cost you anything to participate in the study?
The only cost to you will be your time.

Will you be compensated or receive anything for participating in the study?
You will receive $2 in compensation after completing the questionnaire.

How will your information be kept private?
Your name will never be collected so it cannot be linked to your data.
Your data will be given a randomly assigned number, rather than any identifying information.
The data we collect will be stored electronically in a password protected file. 
Data will always be reported as a group data.  Your information will never be reported by itself.

What will happen with your information once this research study is complete? 
Your answers will be stored, without information that can identify you, and kept for future use. 
These data may be used for additional or subsequent research studies.

What if you don’t want to participate or change your mind partway through? 
Participating in this study is completely voluntary. You may quit this study at any time.

Who can you contact if you have more questions?
If you have any questions about the research, feel free to contact the researchers at kassandradoran@brandeis.edu or knight2@brandeis.edu.


If you have any questions about your rights or have any concerns about the study, please contact the Brandeis University Human Research Protection Program at 781-736-8133 or hrpp-group@brandeis.edu.
